DAVIS CUP FIRST ROUND: USA VS SWITZERLAND
February 3, 2017
Marco Chiudinelli
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
J. SOCK/M. Chiudinelli   
6-4, 6-3, 6-1   
THE MODERATOR: Questions in English, please.   
 Q.  There were a lot of opportunities in the first couple of sets with you at Love-30 on Jack's serve, 15-30.  What made it difficult to move ahead and maybe even get a breakpoint in some early games?  
MARCO CHIUDINELLI: Yeah, actually felt a little bit crazy.  Like you said, so many chances to get the breakpoint I actually did not.   
So struggle a bit with his heavy serve.  Yeah, he had good serves at a lot of those moments.  When I managed to get the ball back, he followed up with some good second shots.   
I remember the 5-3 game second set I think I returned two times well at 15-30, and he just played great points.  So that's credit to him.   
I think I was not really well rewarded for playing two solid sets.  You know, the break I got in the first set, two double faults, and I get unlucky on two very close shots in the break in the second set, 30-All point, let call, and, yeah, he just is a little better.   
I don't think it was such a big difference in the first to sets.  I was disappointed to be down two sets to love.  At the crucial points on his serve he always found a good serve and didn't miss any.  Sometimes you get lucky and the opponent throws in some stupid unforced errors or something.  Credit to him that he did not.   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT